			<h2 style="margin:0;">CERTIFICATE PROGRAMME IN NEWS PROGRAMMES AND DOCUMENTARY FILMMAKING</h2>
<p><strong>Including:</strong> <br />
•	Camera & Editing<br />
•	Scripting, Production<br />
•	Anchoring / Presentation
</p>

<h3>Why ITMI? </h3>

<p class="pad">Documentary filmmaking (on digital and analogue video formats) deals with newsmaking films that go in-depth into burning issues. 
</p>
<p>
As India Today Group’s education wing, ITMI is uniquely poised to deliver new-generation communication courses. Who better to train you in news-related audiovisual production and content than those that are considered the best in the business? With Aaj Tak and India Today channels as two of the top news channels in the nation, many of our faculty members, too, will be from those channels. 

</p>


<p><strong>Programme structure</strong><br />

<strong>Duration:</strong> 96 hours over 4 months<br />

<strong>Days of classes:</strong> Saturdays and Sundays<br />

<strong> Method:</strong> Interactive lectures, lab, assignments, hands-on training.<br />
</p>
<p>
<strong>Delivery:</strong> You will first learn concepts of visual thinking, how to write stories, how to write stories specifically for newsy stuff. </p>
<p>
Simultaneously, you will learn the tools that go into this process—how to use the scripting format, how to shoot and edit, how to conduct interviews, and how to put it all together.

By the end, you will produce a video-format documentary on a topic you choose.</p>
<p><strong>Special value:</strong> You will gain unique exposure to India Today’s high-energy, top-of-the-line studios, and above all, from the group’s high-level expertise. In the real world, you couldn’t ask for more!

</p><p>Certification from the India Today Group.</p>

            
